Currently [VersionRange](https://github.com/NuGet/NuGet.Client/blob/dev/src/NuGet.Core/NuGet.Versioning/VersionRange.cs) class doesn't implement it's own `Equals` method instead use it's base class `VersionRangeBase` which doesn't know anything about floating ranges. So

range1 = new VersionRange("1.0.0"); 
range2 = new VersionRange("1.0.*");

both these ranges are considered equal.
